  <h2 class="sh text-anim">Why neuromorphic.</h2>
  <p class="ss text-anim d1">
    GPUs process every frame whether something changed or not. Cloud inference adds latency. Retraining is a batch process.
    Catalyst neuromorphic processors solve all three by design.
  </p>

  <div class="pillar-stack" style="overflow:visible">

    <!-- 1: EVENT-DRIVEN (image left) -->
    <div class="pcard anim">

      <div class="pcard-img">
        <div class="bg" style="background-image:url('https://images.pexels.com/photos/6755065/pexels-photo-6755065.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=900')"></div>
        <div class="fade"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="pcard-text">
        <span class="pcard-num">01</span>
        <span class="pcard-tag">Architecture</span>
        <h3 class="pcard-h">Event-driven</h3>
        <p class="pcard-p">GPUs run every cycle whether there's input or not. Catalyst cores activate only on events, with no wasted cycles and no wasted power. The architecture is inherently sparse.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 2: ON-CHIP LEARNING (image right) -->
    <div class="pcard anim">

      <div class="pcard-img">
        <div class="bg" style="background-image:url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1550751827-4bd374c3f58b?w=900')"></div>
